@startuml
    skinparam backgroundColor transparent
    skinparam shadowing false
    skinparam nodesep 60
    skinparam ranksep 50
    skinparam componentStyle rectangle
    skinparam arrowThickness 1.5
    skinparam linetype ortho

    title Virtualized Fleet Network for TrackOne Simulation (QEMU/k8s Setup)

    cloud "Host Machine" {
      [User/Admin] as User
      [Wireshark Analyzer] as Wireshark
    }

    package "Kubernetes Cluster (e.g., Minikube)" {

      package "Pod Fleet (Deployment, scaled replicas)" {
        [QEMU Pod 1\n(Firmware in emulation/harness)] as Pod1
        [QEMU Pod 2\n(Firmware in emulation/harness)] as Pod2
        [QEMU Pod N\n(Firmware in emulation/harness)] as PodN

        note bottom of Pod1
        Runs trackone-pod-fw;
        Telemetry over UDP.
        Note: STM32 peripheral fidelity depends on
        the chosen QEMU machine model/harness.
        end note
      }

      [UDP Telemetry Service\n(Service: ClusterIP)] as UdpService
      note bottom of UdpService
      Fleet-to-server UDP ingress.
      Reliability is best-effort unless the
      application protocol adds ACK/retry.
      end note

      [Telemetry Gateway + SensorThings API\n(Deployment)] as Server
      note right of Server
      Parses/framing-validates UDP payloads;
      Maps to OGC SensorThings entities;
      Exposes HTTP API.
      end note

      database "SensorThings Storage\n(Postgres / Timeseries DB)" as DB

      [HTTP API Exposure\n(Service + Ingress/LoadBalancer)] as HttpEdge

      [Sensor Data Generator\n(Job/CronJob, optional)] as Generator
      note left of Generator
      Produces synthetic sensor facts;
      Can emit UDP to the same ingress path.
      end note

      [ConfigMap/Secret\n(config + credentials)] as Config

      package "Observability / Debug (optional)" {
        [Packet Capture\n(DaemonSet or sidecar tcpdump)] as Capture
        note bottom of Capture
        For true packet capture, run capture where the
        packets traverse (node or pod network namespace).
        Port-forward is not L2 sniffing.
        end note
      }
    }

    Pod1 --> UdpService : UDP telemetry\n(port 5678)\n(frame: e.g., COBS/Postcard)
    Pod2 --> UdpService : UDP telemetry
    PodN --> UdpService : UDP telemetry
    Generator ..> UdpService : Optional UDP injection

    UdpService --> Server : UDP to gateway listener
    Server --> DB : Persist\nThings/Datastreams/Observations
    Server --> HttpEdge : HTTP API\n(/Things, /Observations, ...)

    Config ..> Server : env/config
    Config ..> Generator : env/config

    Capture ..> UdpService : capture at node/pod netns
    Wireshark ..> Capture : view pcap (copy/stream)

    User ..> HttpEdge : query API (curl/browser)
    User ..> Generator : trigger job (optional)

    note top of Server
    Time semantics:
    - Ensure node time sync (NTP/chrony) or
      define server-side timestamping rules.
    end note

    @enduml
